00:34:24,520 --> 00:34:28,090
<b>was like a mom, an aunt,</b>

452
00:34:30,160 --> 00:34:32,930
<b>and sometimes a friend.</b>

453
00:34:34,730 --> 00:34:37,700
<b>But she seemed so unfamiliar</b>

454
00:34:38,540 --> 00:34:40,240
<b>and scary today.</b>

455
00:34:41,570 --> 00:34:43,310
<b>[ And that person ]</b>

456
00:34:44,610 --> 00:34:46,780
<b>could have actually...</b>

457
00:34:49,220 --> 00:34:52,550
<b>Did something happen
between you and Ms. Jang?</b>

458
00:34:59,460 --> 00:35:00,830
<b>Should we</b>

459
00:35:01,430 --> 00:35:03,360
<b>just go somewhere far away?</b>

460
00:35:33,860 --> 00:35:36,800
<b>[ Ms. Jang Sun-young ]</b>

461
00:35:38,300 --> 00:35:39,670
<b>[ This is Jang Sun-young. ]</b>

462
00:35:39,700 --> 00:35:40,970
<b>[ Bella disappeared, ]</b>

463
00:35:41,030 --> 00:35:43,040
<b>[ so I'm contacting you,
with all due respect. ]</b>

464
00:35:43,170 --> 00:35:46,710
<b>[ If you happen to know her whereabouts,
please contact me. ]</b>

465
00:36:39,330 --> 00:36:40,930
<b>I'm sorry, Chef Moon.</b>

466
00:36:41,430 --> 00:36:43,330
<b>I fell asleep without realizing.</b>

467
00:36:43,930 --> 00:36:46,830
<b>You must've been tired. You were snoring.</b>

468
00:36:51,270 --> 00:36:52,470
<b>To be honest,</b>

469
00:36:54,040 --> 00:36:58,010
<b>I've never had a happy time in my life.</b>

470
00:37:00,680 --> 00:37:02,920
<b>That's why I couldn't sleep,</b>

471
00:37:03,880 --> 00:37:05,420
<b>nor eat well.</b>

472
00:37:06,990 --> 00:37:09,360
<b>And so I became
this picky and sensitive person.</b>

473
00:37:12,730 --> 00:37:15,030
<b>I've never told Madam Jang,</b>

474
00:37:15,900 --> 00:37:17,060
<b>but I just</b>

475
00:37:18,330 --> 00:37:19,930
<b>wanted to get revenge on everyone.</b>

476
00:37:22,540 --> 00:37:23,740
<b>On who?</b>

477
00:37:26,510 --> 00:37:28,140
<b>Nobody in particular.</b>

478
00:37:29,410 --> 00:37:30,540
<b>Just</b>

479
00:37:31,410 --> 00:37:33,210
<b>to the world</b>

480
00:37:34,650 --> 00:37:36,020
<b>that made me this sad.</b>

481
00:37:40,420 --> 00:37:42,460
<b>Can you let me in on your revenge plan?</b>

482
00:37:45,330 --> 00:37:47,190
<b>Why?</b>

483
00:37:48,560 --> 00:37:51,060
<b>Had my parents not passed away
so suddenly,</b>

484
00:37:52,200 --> 00:37:54,600
<b>I would've never been able to agree
with you.</b>

485
00:37:55,440 --> 00:37:58,570
<b>I never took life seriously.</b>

486
00:38:01,040 --> 00:38:03,610
<b>I just lived as I'd liked.</b>

487
00:38:04,810 --> 00:38:06,250
<b>I thought that was cool,</b>

488
00:38:08,280 --> 00:38:09,950
<b>but I was just immature.</b>

489
00:38:13,590 --> 00:38:16,120
<b>It was only after my parents passed away
when I realized</b>

490
00:38:18,660 --> 00:38:20,030
<b>how selfish</b>

491
00:38:21,490 --> 00:38:23,430
<b>I had been all my life.</b>

492
00:38:27,630 --> 00:38:30,100
<b>I still can't forgive myself for that.</b>

493
00:38:31,770 --> 00:38:33,240
<b>That's why</b>

494
00:38:34,210 --> 00:38:36,240
<b>you've been working so hard
for Pungcheonok.</b>

495
00:38:37,910 --> 00:38:41,050
<b>I wanted to protect that house.</b>

496
00:38:41,650 --> 00:38:43,380
<b>You've been doing well.</b>

497
00:38:44,220 --> 00:38:45,490
<b>I'm proud of you.</b>

498
00:38:49,220 --> 00:38:52,230
<b>To be honest, I'm still scared.</b>

499
00:38:53,360 --> 00:38:55,090
<b>I'm scared that something may happen</b>

500
00:38:55,860 --> 00:39:00,230
<b>and that I may not be able
to stay strong and protect the house.</b>

501
00:39:01,700 --> 00:39:03,870
<b>But you gave me courage.</b>

502
00:39:04,970 --> 00:39:07,010
<b>You made me realize
that even I can protect someone</b>

503
00:39:08,010 --> 00:39:09,980
<b>and that I can be courageous.</b>

504
00:39:11,710 --> 00:39:13,210
<b>You taught me that.</b>

505
00:39:22,060 --> 00:39:23,320
<b>Let's make a promise</b>

506
00:39:24,620 --> 00:39:27,990
<b>that you'll nail the interview today</b>

507
00:39:28,230 --> 00:39:29,830
<b>to protect Belle Ombre</b>

508
00:39:30,930 --> 00:39:34,700
<b>and that going forward, we won't run away
from whatever the future holds.</b>

509
00:39:36,600 --> 00:39:39,440
<b>Instead, we'll stay together
and fight through.</b>

510
00:39:47,310 --> 00:39:48,450
<b>Promise me.</b>

511
00:40:37,900 --> 00:40:39,030
<b>Here.</b>

512
00:40:48,910 --> 00:40:51,710
<b>Dad, you have to pitch well
for me to catch.</b>

513
00:40:52,210 --> 00:40:53,210
<b>Jun-su,</b>

514
00:40:53,280 --> 00:40:56,920
<b>the fun in catching balls comes
from catching curved balls.</b>

515
00:40:58,320 --> 00:40:59,850
<b>You're just a bad pitcher.</b>

516
00:41:02,420 --> 00:41:03,760
<b>Get this!</b>

517
00:41:05,160 --> 00:41:07,330
<b>See? I can do it.</b>

518
00:41:14,370 --> 00:41:15,470
<b>Jun-su,</b>

519
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:18,870
<b>the world won't only throw good pitches
at you.</b>

520
00:41:19,640 --> 00:41:23,110
<b>There's someone who can catch them
and someone who can't.</b>

521
00:41:23,840 --> 00:41:27,210
<b>I hope that you'll grow into a person</b>

522
00:41:27,280 --> 00:41:28,850
<b>who'll catch these curved balls.</b>

523
00:41:29,750 --> 00:41:30,820
<b>Okay!</b>

524
00:41:45,200 --> 00:41:46,400
<b>Yes, Gun-woo?</b>

525
00:41:48,970 --> 00:41:50,070
<b>What?</b>

526
00:41:51,270 --> 00:41:52,810
<b>[ Emergency Representatives' Meeting ]</b>

527
00:41:54,970 --> 00:41:57,840
<b>[ Emergency Representatives' Meeting ]</b>

528
00:41:58,580 --> 00:42:01,780
<b>As someone who's in charge of running
the company</b>

529
00:42:01,810 --> 00:42:04,650
<b>[ since the chairman's passing, ]</b>

530
00:42:05,450 --> 00:42:07,050
<b>I had a lot on my mind.</b>

531
00:42:20,830 --> 00:42:23,800
<b>With the right
as the emergency representative,</b>

532
00:42:23,870 --> 00:42:26,010
<b>I'd like to ask Kang Jun-su
of Donghan Food</b>

533
00:42:27,370 --> 00:42:29,540
<b>to resign from his position</b>

534
00:42:30,640 --> 00:42:31,910
<b>for his professional malpractice.</b>

535
00:42:32,850 --> 00:42:35,150
<b>- Resign?
- What are you talking about?</b>

536
00:42:35,310 --> 00:42:36,380
<b>What do you mean, malpractice?</b>

537
00:42:36,450 --> 00:42:39,850
<b>Donghan Food is currently working</b>

538
00:42:39,920 --> 00:42:42,820
<b>on the Pungcheonok project,
as a part of the old restaurant project.</b>

539
00:42:42,920 --> 00:42:45,630
<b>It's professional malpractice</b>

540
00:42:45,830 --> 00:42:47,960
<b>when you're investing our company's money</b>

541
00:42:48,030 --> 00:42:52,300
<b>on things unrelated to our company
like Pungcheonok.</b>

542
00:42:52,700 --> 00:42:55,100
<b>That's clear professional malpractice.</b>

543
00:42:59,670 --> 00:43:01,070
<b>The Donghan Food shares have gone up</b>

544
00:43:01,140 --> 00:43:03,140
<b>because of gourmandism business,</b>

545
00:43:03,410 --> 00:43:04,940
<b>so how is that malpractice?</b>

546
00:43:05,110 --> 00:43:07,480
<b>Actually, your making
of such an extreme decision</b>

547
00:43:07,550 --> 00:43:09,480
<b>is a damaging act to the company,</b>

548
00:43:09,550 --> 00:43:12,720
<b>which should be brought up
in the next shareholders' meeting.</b>

549
00:43:14,790 --> 00:43:16,060
<b>I'll see you there.</b>

550
00:43:27,300 --> 00:43:28,430
<b>[ What? ]</b>

551
00:43:31,470 --> 00:43:32,570
<b>Don't worry.</b>

552
00:43:33,170 --> 00:43:35,310
<b>He just gave me another reason I can use
to pull him down</b>

553
00:43:35,370 --> 00:43:37,210
<b>from his position at the meeting tomorrow.</b>

554
00:43:38,950 --> 00:43:41,380
<b>Please prepare yourself well
for Louis' interview tonight.</b>

555
00:43:41,680 --> 00:43:42,750
<b>All right.</b>

556
00:43:50,590 --> 00:43:51,820
<b>Lim Chul-yong.</b>

557
00:44:05,870 --> 00:44:06,940
<b>How did it go?</b>

558
00:44:07,010 --> 00:44:09,740
<b>As per your request, we've begun
our construction</b>

559
00:44:09,810 --> 00:44:12,950
<b>on Mount Bongu,
right around Seoha Village.</b>

560
00:44:19,490 --> 00:44:21,890
<b>We should hear from them soon, then.</b>

561
00:44:29,400 --> 00:44:31,060
<b>[ JS Security ]</b>

562
00:44:51,420 --> 00:44:52,720
<b>Let me go!</b>

563
00:44:52,790 --> 00:44:54,020
<b>[ Seriously! ]</b>

564
00:44:54,890 --> 00:44:57,420
<b>My arm!</b>

565
00:44:59,560 --> 00:45:01,630
<b>I'm a busy woman here.
What are we meeting up for?</b>

566
00:45:01,690 --> 00:45:03,600
<b>I looked</b>

567
00:45:03,660 --> 00:45:05,570
<b>into Oh Jung-tae,</b>

568
00:45:05,630 --> 00:45:07,130
<b>the man you asked about.</b>

569
00:45:07,970 --> 00:45:09,970
<b>I've looked through some cases</b>

570
00:45:10,000 --> 00:45:11,700
<b>[ and he seems to be involved
in a lot of them, ]</b>

571
00:45:11,770 --> 00:45:13,640
<b>leaving his fingerprints and blood
here and there.</b>

572
00:45:13,710 --> 00:45:15,210
<b>So thanks to you,</b>

573
00:45:15,270 --> 00:45:17,410
<b>some of these unresolved cases
may get solved.</b>

574
00:45:17,480 --> 00:45:21,550
<b>My supervisor complimented me
on my work for the first time ever.</b>

575
00:45:22,750 --> 00:45:24,380
<b>You came here to show off?</b>

576
00:45:24,450 --> 00:45:26,950
<b>Why do you have to think of it like that?</b>

577
00:45:27,520 --> 00:45:30,120
<b>I'm using it as an excuse to see you,</b>

578
00:45:30,120 --> 00:45:31,520
<b>grab some drinks together,</b>

579
00:45:31,590 --> 00:45:34,530
<b>and show off while at it.</b>

580
00:45:35,630 --> 00:45:37,630
<b>Why are you putting your glasses on?</b>

581
00:45:40,900 --> 00:45:42,230
<b>Are you joking with me?</b>

582
00:45:42,300 --> 00:45:43,640
<b>No...</b>

583
00:45:47,110 --> 00:45:50,140
<b>A couple that has broken up once</b>

584
00:45:50,210 --> 00:45:54,180
<b>will break up for the same reason again
if they get back together.</b>

585
00:45:54,180 --> 00:45:55,280
<b>Do you understand?</b>

586
00:45:56,150 --> 00:45:57,420
<b>Don't you dare call me.</b>

587
00:45:58,220 --> 00:45:59,490
<b>Soon-mi!</b>

588
00:45:59,550 --> 00:46:00,690
<b>Let me go!</b>

589
00:46:01,520 --> 00:46:03,560
<b>You're so mean.</b>

590
00:46:03,620 --> 00:46:05,930
<b>- I'm sorry.
[ - Gosh. ]</b>

591
00:46:07,560 --> 00:46:10,230
<b>[ Case Title: Pungcheonok Fire Accident ]</b>

592
00:46:16,700 --> 00:46:17,970
<b>[ Pungcheonok, Closed for Today ]</b>

593
00:46:18,040 --> 00:46:19,440
<b>[ Emergency! ]</b>

594
00:46:19,910 --> 00:46:22,210
<b>What emergency?</b>

595
00:46:22,270 --> 00:46:24,280
<b>[ Donghan International gave notice
to the county office ]</b>

596
00:46:24,340 --> 00:46:26,880
<b>[ that they'll start building
their clothing industrial complex ]</b>

597
00:46:26,950 --> 00:46:30,850
<b>[ starting from Mount Bongu,
which is their property. ]</b>

598
00:46:30,920 --> 00:46:32,420
<b>What are you talking about?</b>

599
00:46:32,490 --> 00:46:34,450
<b>- Tell us more.
- Explain.</b>

600
00:46:34,520 --> 00:46:36,090
<b>- What are you talking about?
- Tell us.</b>

601
00:46:36,160 --> 00:46:38,690
<b>Go outside and look! It's a disaster.</b>

602
00:46:38,760 --> 00:46:40,490
<b>- Why?
- Come quickly!</b>

603
00:46:40,560 --> 00:46:41,860
<b>Come!</b>

604
00:46:41,930 --> 00:46:44,230
<b>- We're heading outside right now.
- How can this be?</b>

605
00:46:44,300 --> 00:46:46,400
<b>What is this nonsense?</b>

606
00:46:46,600 --> 00:46:48,630
<b>There are excavators</b>

607
00:46:48,700 --> 00:46:50,640
<b>coming in right now.</b>

608
00:46:50,700 --> 00:46:53,840
<b>- There are so many.
- Why are they coming to our village?</b>

609
00:46:53,910 --> 00:46:56,380
<b>- Why are they doing this?
- Hold on.</b>

610
00:46:56,410 --> 00:46:58,840
<b>Hey! Where do you think you're going?</b>

611
00:46:59,050 --> 00:47:01,480
<b>- It's a disaster.
- Where are they going?</b>

612
00:47:01,550 --> 00:47:02,680
<b>Goodness!</b>

613
00:47:02,750 --> 00:47:04,580
<b>[ We can't stop them from doing ]</b>

614
00:47:04,650 --> 00:47:06,550
<b>[ whatever they want
on their own territory. ]</b>

615
00:47:06,790 --> 00:47:07,690
<b>What?</b>

616
00:47:07,850 --> 00:47:11,590
<b>So, they're just going to dig Mount Bongu</b>

617
00:47:11,660 --> 00:47:13,990
<b>and not our village, right?</b>

618
00:47:16,430 --> 00:47:19,130
<b>[ Why aren't you saying anything? ]</b>

619
00:47:19,230 --> 00:47:21,800
<b>Are they going to destroy our village
or not?</b>

620
00:47:21,900 --> 00:47:24,000
<b>We'll see how things progress.</b>

621
00:47:24,070 --> 00:47:25,810
<b>Progress?</b>

622
00:47:25,840 --> 00:47:29,180
<b>You have to help us out.</b>

623
00:47:29,240 --> 00:47:30,910
<b>Now that you're bringing it up,</b>

624
00:47:30,980 --> 00:47:32,380
<b>when have I ever not helped you?</b>

625
00:47:32,450 --> 00:47:35,410
<b>I signed the MOU with Donghan Food,
brought the provincial governor,</b>

626
00:47:35,480 --> 00:47:37,850
<b>and did everything I could to promote
Pungcheonok.</b>

627
00:47:37,920 --> 00:47:40,690
<b>Yes, you're right.</b>

628
00:47:41,190 --> 00:47:43,290
<b>Since you've helped us a lot,</b>

629
00:47:43,360 --> 00:47:45,760
<b>stay with us through this.</b>

630
00:47:45,830 --> 00:47:47,660
<b>A civil servant surely can't</b>

631
00:47:47,730 --> 00:47:50,100
<b>go back on his words, right?</b>

632
00:47:50,160 --> 00:47:52,060
<b>Goodness.</b>

633
00:47:52,160 --> 00:47:54,400
<b>I'm not the one going back on my words,</b>

634
00:47:54,470 --> 00:47:56,700
<b>Donghan Food is.</b>

635
00:47:56,770 --> 00:47:57,900
<b>What?</b>

636
00:47:57,940 --> 00:47:59,940
<b>What are you talking about?</b>

637
00:48:00,010 --> 00:48:01,270
<b>Oh, my.</b>

638
00:48:01,340 --> 00:48:03,140
<b>Seems like you guys haven't heard yet.</b>

639
00:48:03,210 --> 00:48:05,240
<b>The managing director of Donghan Food
got fired.</b>

640
00:48:05,310 --> 00:48:08,710
<b>Their gourmandism business is no longer
on the table.</b>

641
00:48:08,750 --> 00:48:12,790
<b>- What?
- What nonsense is this?</b>

642
00:48:19,020 --> 00:48:20,490
<b>We're here, Yu-jin.</b>

643
00:48:21,330 --> 00:48:22,490
<b>Thank you.</b>

644
00:48:30,740 --> 00:48:31,700
<b>Yes, Da-hoon?</b>

645
00:48:31,770 --> 00:48:33,310
<b>There are excavators coming in</b>

646
00:48:33,370 --> 00:48:35,880
<b>and digging through Mount Bongu right now!</b>

647
00:48:35,940 --> 00:48:37,810
<b>How can all of this happen
just within a day?</b>

648
00:48:37,880 --> 00:48:39,680
<b>What are you talking about?</b>

649
00:48:39,710 --> 00:48:41,380
<b>Calm down and tell me again.</b>

650
00:48:41,380 --> 00:48:44,120
<b>Donghan International is building</b>

651
00:48:44,120 --> 00:48:45,550
<b>a clothing industrial complex</b>

652
00:48:45,620 --> 00:48:48,050
<b>and they've started on it right now.</b>

653
00:48:48,120 --> 00:48:49,360
<b>They're building the complex?</b>

654
00:48:49,420 --> 00:48:51,390
<b>[ Yes! All the elders are so mad, ]</b>

655
00:48:51,460 --> 00:48:53,630
<b>[ they're saying that they're heading
to Seoul right now. ]</b>

656
00:48:53,660 --> 00:48:55,660
<b>[ Make your choice, Yoo Yu-jin. ]</b>

657
00:48:56,160 --> 00:48:57,730
<b>Is it Belle Ombre</b>

658
00:48:59,630 --> 00:49:01,200
<b>or Seoha Village?</b>

659
00:49:02,170 --> 00:49:03,370
<b>You want to come to Seoul?</b>

660
00:49:03,400 --> 00:49:04,970
<b>Why would you come here?</b>

661
00:49:05,040 --> 00:49:06,340
<b>I'm here, so I'll meet up with</b>

662
00:49:06,410 --> 00:49:08,210
<b>Mr. Kang and hear what's going on.</b>

663
00:49:08,270 --> 00:49:10,180
<b>[ Mr. Kang got fired! ]</b>

664
00:49:10,240 --> 00:49:11,410
<b>What?</b>

665
00:49:11,680 --> 00:49:13,980
<b>All right. I'll talk to you later.</b>

666
00:49:18,720 --> 00:49:20,290
<b>Go, Chef Moon.</b>

667
00:49:20,590 --> 00:49:22,050
<b>[ Don't worry. ]</b>

668
00:49:22,220 --> 00:49:24,420
<b>I'm just going to go upstairs</b>

669
00:49:24,520 --> 00:49:26,360
<b>and talk things out with Madam Jang.</b>

670
00:49:26,430 --> 00:49:27,660
<b>[ I'll be fine, really. ]</b>

671
00:49:39,340 --> 00:49:40,740
<b>Chef Moon,</b>

672
00:49:42,170 --> 00:49:43,810
<b>you'll stay with me</b>

673
00:49:44,040 --> 00:49:47,210
<b>whatever choice I make, right?</b>

674
00:49:52,120 --> 00:49:53,320
<b>I'll be right back.</b>

675
00:50:06,570 --> 00:50:07,770
<b>[ Chef Moon Seung-mo ]</b>

676
00:50:07,830 --> 00:50:09,130
<b>[ This is Jang Sun-young. ]</b>

677
00:50:13,170 --> 00:50:17,410
<b>Bella is Bella.
She's always so unpredictable.</b>

678
00:50:18,680 --> 00:50:19,710
<b>I'm sorry.</b>

679
00:50:19,780 --> 00:50:22,950
<b>Will I be able to see Bella
before the interview</b>

680
00:50:23,020 --> 00:50:25,250
<b>as promised?</b>

681
00:50:25,280 --> 00:50:27,590
<b>- Absolutely.
- As I've said before,</b>

682
00:50:27,750 --> 00:50:30,460
<b>I won't do the interview</b>

683
00:50:30,490 --> 00:50:33,290
<b>unless I see Bella beforehand.</b>

684
00:50:38,030 --> 00:50:39,130
<b>Bella?</b>

685
00:50:42,430 --> 00:50:43,900
<b>The interview is tonight,</b>

686
00:50:43,970 --> 00:50:45,270
<b>but you don't know where she is?</b>

687
00:50:45,340 --> 00:50:47,140
<b>What is this nonsense?</b>

688
00:50:52,040 --> 00:50:53,610
<b>I have nothing to say.</b>

689
00:50:53,650 --> 00:50:55,710
<b>This interview was so difficult to get!</b>

690
00:51:04,120 --> 00:51:05,520
<b>Apart from the project itself,</b>

691
00:51:05,590 --> 00:51:07,760
<b>I should've protected Seoha Village
until the end.</b>

692
00:51:08,890 --> 00:51:10,130
<b>I'm sorry.</b>

693
00:51:10,360 --> 00:51:12,430
<b>Then what happens to Seoha Village?</b>

694
00:51:12,800 --> 00:51:14,570
<b>It's not over yet.</b>

695
00:51:14,700 --> 00:51:17,670
<b>As you know,
if Bella does the interview tonight,</b>

696
00:51:17,740 --> 00:51:19,610
<b>we can take Mr. Lim down.</b>

697
00:51:19,840 --> 00:51:23,240
<b>This may be his last fight
before he goes down.</b>

698
00:51:24,610 --> 00:51:26,480
<b>Seems like fate is in Bella's hands.</b>

699
00:51:27,150 --> 00:51:28,380
<b>Bella can save both her company</b>

700
00:51:28,450 --> 00:51:29,850
<b>and Seoha Village.</b>

701
00:51:29,850 --> 00:51:30,950
<b>I know.</b>

702
00:51:31,520 --> 00:51:32,750
<b>I know, but...</b>

703
00:51:41,460 --> 00:51:42,760
<b>All right.</b>

704
00:51:44,500 --> 00:51:46,400
<b>The village people are very shocked
right now.</b>

705
00:51:46,430 --> 00:51:48,470
<b>I'll let them know what you said.</b>

706
00:52:05,080 --> 00:52:06,720
<b>It'll be all right, right?</b>

707
00:52:07,490 --> 00:52:08,450
<b>What is?</b>

708
00:52:08,520 --> 00:52:10,220
<b>Say that Bella does the interview</b>

709
00:52:10,290 --> 00:52:12,520
<b>and takes a big blow on Mr. Lim.</b>

710
00:52:12,890 --> 00:52:13,990
<b>But if he tries</b>

711
00:52:14,060 --> 00:52:16,800
<b>to stay in power through lawsuits,</b>

712
00:52:16,930 --> 00:52:19,430
<b>then we'll never know
when this fight will end.</b>

713
00:52:20,230 --> 00:52:22,030
<b>Seoha Village could be gone</b>

714
00:52:22,100 --> 00:52:24,140
<b>in the meantime.</b>

715
00:52:24,600 --> 00:52:25,900
<b>We have no other choice.</b>

716
00:52:26,370 --> 00:52:29,370
<b>What's important right now is</b>

717
00:52:29,740 --> 00:52:32,580
<b>to stop Mr. Lim from becoming
the chairman of the company.</b>

718
00:52:41,020 --> 00:52:42,390
<b>Mr. Lim.</b>

719
00:52:46,990 --> 00:52:48,990
<b>Yes, you're the head of Seoha Village.</b>

720
00:52:53,230 --> 00:52:54,800
<b>What brings you here?</b>

721
00:52:54,870 --> 00:52:56,940
<b>I heard that the gourmandism business
has been halted</b>

722
00:52:57,000 --> 00:52:59,510
<b>and that you're working
on the clothing industrial complex again,</b>

723
00:52:59,570 --> 00:53:00,840
<b>which is what brings me here.</b>

724
00:53:00,910 --> 00:53:04,480
<b>Right, the clothing industrial complex.</b>

725
00:53:04,610 --> 00:53:06,910
<b>That all depends on Yu-jin.</b>

726
00:53:07,410 --> 00:53:08,580
<b>What?</b>

727
00:53:08,850 --> 00:53:10,120
<b>What are you talking about?</b>

728
00:53:10,180 --> 00:53:11,280
<b>Oh, my.</b>

729
00:53:11,880 --> 00:53:14,690
<b>I'm guessing that you haven't heard yet.</b>

730
00:53:16,790 --> 00:53:20,630
<b>Yu-jin holds the village very close
to her heart.</b>

731
00:53:21,060 --> 00:53:25,130
<b>When I said that I'd be resuming
the clothing industrial complex project,</b>

732
00:53:26,170 --> 00:53:30,770
<b>she looked so sad as if she's going
to stop impersonating Bella.</b>

733
00:53:33,270 --> 00:53:35,510
<b>What did you say to her?</b>

734
00:53:40,750 --> 00:53:44,120
<b>"Is it Belle Ombre or Seoha Village?"</b>

735
00:53:45,680 --> 00:53:47,590
<b>I told her to choose.</b>

736
00:53:49,460 --> 00:53:53,990
<b>That was very kind of me,
considering that she's a swindler.</b>

737
00:53:58,330 --> 00:54:00,530
<b>How dare you call her a swindler?</b>

738
00:54:00,930 --> 00:54:02,570
<b>You think you can get away with this?</b>

739
00:54:11,310 --> 00:54:13,880
<b>I just helped her</b>

740
00:54:14,910 --> 00:54:17,450
<b>to get her head straight.</b>

741
00:54:27,930 --> 00:54:29,090
<b>Yu-jin...</b>

742
00:54:44,930 --> 00:54:48,460
<b>One of Bella's worst habits is</b>

743
00:54:49,160 --> 00:54:53,270
<b>to disappear before the event
then appears before it starts.</b>

744
00:54:53,400 --> 00:54:56,840
<b>If we wait, she'll definitely come.</b>

745
00:54:57,210 --> 00:54:58,370
<b>She'd better come.</b>

746
00:54:58,970 --> 00:55:01,010
<b>This isn't just about Belle Ombre,</b>

747
00:55:01,810 --> 00:55:03,810
<b>this is also about Donghan Group.</b>

748
00:55:07,520 --> 00:55:08,980
<b>Have a seat.</b>

749
00:55:39,520 --> 00:55:41,320
<b>[ If you give up being Bella ]</b>

750
00:55:41,380 --> 00:55:44,850
<b>and everything in Belle Ombre,</b>

751
00:55:46,050 --> 00:55:48,120
<b>you can have Mount Bongu,</b>

752
00:55:48,190 --> 00:55:50,490
<b>the Yoo family gravesite.</b>

753
00:55:51,990 --> 00:55:55,460
<b>That's a quite logical tradeoff.</b>

754
00:56:00,970 --> 00:56:04,040
<b>[ Name: Yoo Yu-jin ]</b>

755
00:56:11,910 --> 00:56:13,780
<b>[ DBC ]</b>

756
00:56:16,220 --> 00:56:17,420
<b>Where have you been?</b>

757
00:56:19,190 --> 00:56:22,990
<b>At last, my friend. Bella!</b>

758
00:56:23,190 --> 00:56:24,690
<b>Nice to see you, Louis.</b>

759
00:56:26,500 --> 00:56:27,830
<b>Sorry to interrupt,</b>

760
00:56:27,900 --> 00:56:30,670
<b>but let's talk after the interview.</b>

761
00:56:33,670 --> 00:56:36,140
<b>- Anything wrong?
- I don't know.</b>

762
00:56:40,140 --> 00:56:42,910
<b>Where have you been?</b>

763
00:56:42,980 --> 00:56:46,050
<b>Do you know how long we've waited for you?
You should've at least called.</b>

764
00:56:46,180 --> 00:56:47,580
<b>Why did you wait?</b>

765
00:56:48,320 --> 00:56:49,450
<b>What?</b>

766
00:56:49,650 --> 00:56:51,250
<b>Were you worried about me</b>

767
00:56:51,390 --> 00:56:54,490
<b>or were you worried about
not getting Belle Ombre back?</b>

768
00:56:55,260 --> 00:56:57,560
<b>What are you talking about?</b>

769
00:56:58,690 --> 00:57:00,830
<b>[ - We're makeup artists. ]
- Please come in.</b>

770
00:57:05,670 --> 00:57:08,340
<b>Can you get out so that I can get ready?</b>

771
00:57:09,910 --> 00:57:11,870
<b>We'll talk after the interview.</b>

772
00:57:24,120 --> 00:57:26,590
<b>[ Chef Moon Seung-mo ]</b>

773
00:57:29,890 --> 00:57:32,230
<b>[ Chef Moon Seung-mo ]</b>

774
00:57:40,900 --> 00:57:42,600
<b>[ Yu-jin ]</b>

775
00:57:43,710 --> 00:57:44,910
<b>Yu-jin...</b>

776
00:57:46,880 --> 00:57:48,010
<b>[ Chef Moon, ]</b>

777
00:57:48,780 --> 00:57:50,010
<b>you'll stay with me</b>

778
00:57:50,680 --> 00:57:53,680
<b>whatever choice I make, right?</b>

779
00:58:00,120 --> 00:58:02,020
<b>[ DBC ]</b>

780
00:58:11,900 --> 00:58:13,100
<b>What brings you here?</b>

781
00:58:24,480 --> 00:58:25,910
<b>Chef Moon?</b>

782
00:58:27,180 --> 00:58:29,120
<b>She can't talk right now.</b>

783
00:58:29,180 --> 00:58:30,390
<b>Maybe you can talk later.</b>

784
00:58:32,590 --> 00:58:35,590
<b>You have to stop Bella from doing
her interview? What are you talking about?</b>

785
00:58:36,160 --> 00:58:37,990
<b>[ Coming up next, ]</b>

786
00:58:38,060 --> 00:58:41,230
<b>[ we have an interview with Chairman Louis
of Louis Bellemont ]</b>

787
00:58:41,300 --> 00:58:45,000
<b>[ and Bella, his chosen designer. ]</b>

788
00:58:45,530 --> 00:58:47,900
<b>[ Chairman Louis will be talking ]</b>

789
00:58:47,970 --> 00:58:49,470
<b>[ about Bella's identity ]</b>

790
00:58:49,540 --> 00:58:52,940
<b>[ and we'll also be hearing
from Yoo Yu-jin, the real Bella. ]</b>

791
00:58:53,340 --> 00:58:54,980
<b>[ DBC News will... ]</b>

792
00:58:55,040 --> 00:58:58,010
<b>I wonder what she's going to say.</b>

793
00:59:07,990 --> 00:59:11,230
<b>[ Chairman Louis Bellemont
and his chosen designer Yoo Yu-jin, Bella ]</b>

794
00:59:12,630 --> 00:59:13,760
<b>Chef Moon.</b>

795
00:59:14,230 --> 00:59:16,830
<b>- Please let him in.
- It's okay, you can let him in.</b>

796
00:59:20,800 --> 00:59:22,000
<b>What's happening?</b>

797
00:59:22,070 --> 00:59:24,270
<b>- Which floor is the studio on?
- The fifth floor.</b>

798
00:59:27,810 --> 00:59:28,910
<b>Chef Moon!</b>

799
00:59:56,300 --> 00:59:57,410
<b>[ Yu-jin! ]</b>

800
01:00:10,650 --> 01:00:12,620
<b>Ms. Yoo Yu-jin, please come this way.</b>

801
01:00:23,230 --> 01:00:24,930
<b>Don't do it.</b>

802
01:00:27,340 --> 01:00:29,040
<b>I have to head inside.</b>

803
01:00:30,040 --> 01:00:40,040
<b></b>

804
01:01:06,880 --> 01:01:10,880
<b>[ Eccentric! Chef Moon ]</b>

805
01:01:11,080 --> 01:01:14,820
<b>I made the clothing that
was chosen as the real Bella's design.</b>

806
01:01:14,880 --> 01:01:16,480
<b>- Yes!
- Yes!</b>

807
01:01:17,320 --> 01:01:18,520
<b>How could you?</b>

808
01:01:18,850 --> 01:01:20,060
<b>[ You want me to stop? ]</b>

809
01:01:20,190 --> 01:01:23,930
<b>Then you should've kept it a secret
from me until the end.</b>

810
01:01:24,060 --> 01:01:25,090
<b>What about the proof?</b>

811
01:01:25,090 --> 01:01:26,830
<b>I checked the recording.</b>

812
01:01:26,900 --> 01:01:28,360
<b>You really don't listen.</b>

813
01:01:28,430 --> 01:01:30,570
<b>Sorry, but that's up to me.</b>

814
01:01:30,630 --> 01:01:33,000
<b>I hope that you'll be happy. I love you.</b>

815
01:01:34,340 --> 01:01:35,500
<b>Yu-jin!</b>

816
01:01:35,740 --> 01:01:38,210
<b>[ You always have to have your way
and you're so much in trouble. ]</b>

817
01:01:38,270 --> 01:01:39,470
<b>But</b>

818
01:01:40,180 --> 01:01:42,110
<b>[ that's what I like about you. ]</b>

819
01:01:43,480 --> 01:01:44,750
<b>I like you.</b>

